<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<configuration>
  <runtime>
    <!--
      Tekla.* assemblies are supplied at runtime by TeklaAssemblyResolver (see Program.cs):
      each release is built for ONE Tekla version (issue #11) and the resolver LoadFrom's the
      matching DLLs from the installed Tekla's bin, failing fast on a version mismatch.

      Do NOT add bindingRedirects for Tekla.* here:
        - Per-version builds don't need them. A strong-named bind is satisfied only by the
          exact compiled version, so a different-version GAC copy can never hijack the bind
          (the issue #7 failure mode), and a same-version one is protocol-compatible.
        - The old 2999.9.9.9 anti-GAC redirect trick is actively harmful with any resolver
          that loads images from bytes: on .NET Framework, Assembly.Load(byte[]) APPLIES
          binding policy to the image's identity, so the redirect turns the resolver's own
          load into a bind for 2999.9.9.9 — a circular resolve that ends in
          FileNotFound/StackOverflow (verified live, twice: cbe716b and the d167ff4
          re-attempt reverted right after). See docs/tekla-api-notes.md.
    -->
  </runtime>
</configuration>
